  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Living Conditions and Protection of Conflict-affected Populations in North-East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM will contribute to ensuring an adequate humanitarian and recovery response to the needs of IDPs, host communities and returnees in North-Eastern Nigeria. The action will expand the reach of life-saving and recovery activities that IOM is currently providing to IDPs, returnees and affected communities in the North-East of Nigeria. In particular, this project will: provide psychosocial support, strengthen camp management and coordination capacities; provide Non-Food Items (NFI), Water, Sanitation and Hygiene assistance and emergency shelter solutions to displaced population including the upgrade and reinforcement of the existing dilapidated shelters in displacement sites; expand cash-based interventions in orderto contribute to the early recovery of affected populations. In addition, IOM will support the maintenance, running and improvement of nine humanitarian hubs in Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
